# InstanceCollectionHelper
This document describes changes to each version of **InstanceCollectionHelper (ICH)** and will be updated with each new release.

Release versions suffixed with a lowercase letter are considered unofficial _alpha_ or _early access_ versions.

## Changes
**v8**
- Fixed a bug causing mounts to not display when using the search bar

**v7**
- **Major update:** Added tabs at the bottom of the window to switch between viewing mounts and toys available from instances
- **Major update:** Added a list of toys that are available from dungeons and raids as of Patch 11.2 (Ghosts of K'aresh)
- Updated all tooltips to match the one shown in-game for the given collectible
- Refactored code and made minor updates to the UI so that both mounts and toys can be accomodated
- Updated localization strings for supported locales (_still looking for translators!_)
- Updated the icon used for indicating a note on a list item
- Updated AddOn description (_README.md_) and code documentation

**v6**
- Created an "About" window for crediting translators and providing contact info for the AddOn
- Added a button for opening the "About" window with an _info_ icon
- Updated the icon for the "How to Use" tooltip of the AddOn to a _question mark_
- Updated the search bar functionality to filter results more accurately in all languages
- Minor code refactoring

**v5**
- Added Unbound Star-Eater from Manaforge Omega
- Fixed an issue that sometimes caused an error when viewing the note for **Cartel Master's Gearglider**
 
**v4**
- Added support for `zhCN` locale (_still looking for translators!_)

**v3**
- Added support for `zhTW` locale (_still looking for translators!_)
- Added a note about Karazhan's instance difficulty being 10 player by default regardless of player's settings
- Fixed a translation error where English users would see the note for Tazavesh in German

**v2**
- Added support for **TomTom** waypoints to be dropped at instance entrances with one click
- Added support for `ptBR` and `deDE` locales (_still looking for translators!_)
- Update AddOn for Patch 11.2 compatibility
- Improved text localization for all supported locales
- Documentation updates

**v1**
- Added ability to set Blizzard map pins on instance entrances
- Added support for `esMX` locale (_still looking for more translators!_)
- Updated AddOn UI and tooltip text
- Documentation updates

**v8b**
- Added a missing required dependency to the embedded files of the AddOn
- Minor code cleanup and documentation updates
- Set up framework for localization into non-English languages (_looking for translators!_)

**v8a**
- Update slash commands for setting instance difficulty to display a message when the chosen difficulty is already set
- Fix bug causing slider arrows to not resize the AddOn window
- Reduce minimum allowed value for UI slider to decrease window size beyond default

**v7a**
- Create a "search hints" tooltip to provide examples of how to use the search functionality
- Move the text explaining how the AddOn works into a tooltip
- Create buttons for both "search hints" and "how it works" to show the appropriate tooltip
- Added option to increase the UI size as desired
- Added an option to show owned mounts in the list (indicated with a green background)

**v6a**
- Added a search bar to filter the list of available mounts
- Fixed some typos in instance names
- Added LFR button for tracking completed Raid Finder lockouts
- Update difficulty buttons to be disabled when legacy raid is completed on a different difficulty (shared difficulty lockouts)

**v5a**
- Add difficulty button for **Ashes of Al'ar** to help track weekly lockout
- Added slash commands to update instance difficulty from chat window:
  - `/ich dung` for dungeons
  - `/ich raid` for raids
  - `/ich lraid` for legacy raids
- Updated notes for some mounts

**v4a**
- Update AddOn logo
- Add missing mounts to list
- Update difficulty button colors
- Update some mount-related data
- Added command `/ich diffs` to view all instance difficulty settings at once

**v3a**
- Fixed a bug where _Blizzard_ boss names sometimes didn't correctly match what Blizzard calls the boss in the Encounter Journal
- Updated dependencies that caused issues on load sometimes
- Updated the list to show correct lockout info immediately after opening

**v2b**
- Load necessary _Blizzard_ AddOns when initializing

**v2a**
- Fix bug where owned mounts weren't updated automatically on login

**v1a**
- Initial release